SPINNERETS. PMS: length 0.63; diameter 0.35. PLS: maximal diameter 0.70; length of basal, medial and apical segments 1.10, 0.77, 1.02; total length 2.89; apical segment shortly digitiform (
Fig. 65
).

SPERMATHECAE. Low and broad, with very widely spaced receptacles (
Fig. 201
).

Carapace length in males varies from 7.25 to 8.57, in females from 6.88 to 10.13. In some females, the dorsal abdominal pattern is almost indistinct. Spermathecae show a quite insignificant variation (cf. 
Figs 200–201
).
